text:
The attached patch cleans the lang/mono port a bit:
  - Remove unneeded CONFIGURE_ARGS;
  - Make use of USE_GETTEXT since we install .po files;
  - OPTIONify the Moonlight profile (was unconditionally added because of a typo);
  - Keep pkg-plist sorted;
  - Update the pkg-message by not mentioning FreeBSD 5.X anymore and giving information for jailing mono.

Tinderbuilt and installed on my system (i386).
